Enum Class Rank

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<Rank>
edu.wit.scds.ds.lists.app.card_game.standard_cards.card.Rank
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Rank>, Constable
public enum Rank extends Enum<Rank>
An enumeration of card ranks.
Version:
1.0 2016-03-16 initial version, 1.1 2022-11-06 add switches for standard vs alternate points and order, 2.0 2025-03-29
  • add abbreviated name to support user selection
  • revise interpretDescription to select based on abbreviated name rather than hardcoded values
  • add displayHelp() to support user specification/selection
  • add various public "USE_" constants to support more mnemonic programming
, 7.0 2025-06-26
  • rename from Rank to Rank to track other class changes
  • swap (alt) point and (alt) order values
Author:
David M Rosenberg

  • Constructor Details

    • Rank

      private Rank(String rankDisplayName, String rankAbbreviatedName, String rankGraphic, int rankPoints, int rankAltPoints, int rankOrder, int rankAltOrder)
      Sets all fields representing a card rank
      Parameters:
      rankDisplayName - more esthetically pleasing for display
      rankAbbreviatedName - abbreviation for the rank, typically used for user suit selection
      rankGraphic - the 'standard' icon
      rankPoints - numeric value for the card
      rankAltPoints - alternate value for the card (e.g., Ace can be worth 1 or 11 points)
      rankOrder - numeric order for the card
      rankAltOrder - alternate order for the card (e.g., Ace can have the lowest or highest order)
